        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Numbers 20</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num020-P246v-L14_trl" n="14"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.004.019.trl.xml#Num019-P246v-L14_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             the children of Israel, all the congregation, came to the wilderness of
                            Zin in the first
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             month, and the people stayed in Kadesh. And Miriam died there
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and was buried there.</l>
                        <l n="2">And there was no water for the congregation,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             and they gathered themselves against Moses and against Aaron.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="3">And the people quarrelled with Moses, and said, saying,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             ‘If only we have passed away when our brothers passed away
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             before the Lord!</l>
                        <l n="4">And why have you brought the assembly
                            <milestone unit="page" n="247r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             of the Lord to this wilderness to die there, we and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             our cattle?</l>
                        <l n="5">And why have you brought us out from Egypt
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             to bring us to this bad place? It is no place
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             of sowing or of figs or of vines or of pomegranates, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             there is even no water to drink.’</l>
                        <l n="6">And Moses and Aaron came
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             from before the assembly to the door of the tent of meeting, and they
                            fell
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             on their faces, and the divine Presence of the Lord appeared
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             to them.</l>
                        <l n="7">And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="8">‘Take the staff and gather the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             congregation together, you and Aaron, your brother, and speak to the
                            rock
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             in the sight of them, and it shall give its water. And you shall bring
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             water out of the rock for them, and you shall give a drink to the
                            congregation and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             their livestock.’</l>
                        <l n="9">And Moses took the staff
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             from before the Lord as he commanded him.</l>
                        <l n="10">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             Moses and Aaron gathered the assembly together before the rock, and he
                            said
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             to them, ‘Hear now, oh rebels: shall we bring out water of this rock
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             for you?’</l>
                        <l n="11">And Moses lifted his hand and struck
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             the rock with his staff twice. And much water came out.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             And the congregation and their livestock drank.</l>
                        <l n="12">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             the Lord said to Moses and Aaron, ‘Because you did not carry out
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             my order with confidence to show my holiness, <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Num-020-seg001_trl" />to speak
                            <milestone unit="page" n="247v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             to the rock that it may give you water<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Num-020-seg001_trl" /><ref n="1" target="#Num-020-fn1_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" /> in the sight of the children of Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             therefore you will not bring this assembly
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             to the land which I have given them.’</l>
                        <l n="13">These are the waters <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Num-020-seg002_trl" />of quarrel<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Num-020-seg002_trl" /><ref n="2" target="#Num-020-fn2_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" />,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             because the children of Israel quarrelled before the Lord, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             he showed his holiness among them.</l>
                        <l n="14">And Moses sent
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             envoys from Kadesh to the lord of Edom, ‘Thus says your brother
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             Israel: You know all the tiredness that has befallen us.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="15">And our fathers went down to Egypt, and we have stayed
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             in Egypt many days. And the people of Egypt was bad to us
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and also to our fathers,</l>
                        <l n="16">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             we cried to the Lord and he heard our voice and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             he sent an envoy and he has brought us out from Egypt. And, lo, we
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             are in Kadesh, a city on the edge of your border.</l>
                        <l n="17">Let us pass,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             now, through your land. We will not pass through the fields or through
                            the vineyards,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             and we will not drink well waters. We will go by the king’s road,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             we will not turn to the right hand nor to the left, until
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             we pass your border.’</l>
                        <l n="18">And Edom said to him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             ‘You will not pass through my land, lest I come out against you with
                            the sword.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="19">And the children of Israel said to him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             ‘We will go by the way, and if I and my livestock drink of your water,
                            then
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             I will give their price. Only, there is nothing more, let me pass
                            through on foot.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="248r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="20">And he said, ‘You will not go through.’ And Edom came out
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             against him with much people, and with a strong hand.</l>
                        <l n="21">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             And Edom did not want to empower Israel to pass
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             through his border. And Israel turned away from him.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="22">And they set out from Kadesh, and the children
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             of Israel, the whole congregation, came to Mount Hor.</l>
                        <l n="23">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             the Lord said to Moses and Aaron at Mount Hor, by the border
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             of the land of Edom, saying,</l>
                        <l n="24">‘Aaron shall be gathered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             to his people, for he will not come to the land which I have given
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             to the children of Israel, because you rebelled against my command
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             in the matter at the water <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Num-020-seg003_trl" />of quarrel<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Num-020-seg003_trl" /><ref n="3" target="#Num-020-fn3_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="25">Take Aaron
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             and Eleazar, his son, and bring them up
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             to Mount Hor.</l>
                        <l n="26">And you shall take off Aaron’s
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             garments, and you shall put them on Eleazar, his son.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             And Aaron shall be gathered and die there.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="27">And Moses did as the Lord commanded. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             they went up to Mount Hor in the sight of all <supplied reason="lost"
                                >the congregation</supplied>.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="28">And Moses took of Aaron’s
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             garments and put them on Eleazar, his son.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             And Aaron died there on the top of the mountain. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             Moses and Eleazar came down from the mountain. </l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
